You knew?

56:23.630 --> 56:24.672
You psycho wench…

56:24.756 --> 56:25.715
<i>Isn't it astounding?</i>

56:26.299 --> 56:28.760
<i>Using the virus
that doesn't even exist as an excuse</i>

56:28.843 --> 56:31.012
to drag people away and sell them
off for human experiments.

56:34.140 --> 56:37.143
Only one creative psycho
could have come up with that.

56:37.227 --> 56:40.313
-This is all manipulated.
-I truly admire you, Mr. President.

56:40.396 --> 56:42.565
You're all being deceived. Hold on.

56:42.649 --> 56:45.401
My fellow Koreans
whom I deeply love and respect,

56:45.485 --> 56:49.072
all these videos are manipulated!
This is an anti-government movement

56:49.155 --> 56:51.407
to try and overthrow
the current government…

56:51.491 --> 56:53.535
<i>I've been telling you time and time again</i>

56:53.618 --> 56:56.371
<i>that it's the people that matter
the most, have I not?</i>

56:56.454 --> 56:59.666
<i>All these people here are all money.</i>

56:59.749 --> 57:01.251
<i>Those clinical trials?</i>

57:01.334 --> 57:03.837
<i>Do you know how much they are
bringing in per head? It's no joke!</i>

57:03.920 --> 57:07.132
<i>And if they should die,
we harvest everything we can from them!</i>

57:07.215 --> 57:11.636
<i>Oh, and their hair, blood,
and other by-products…</i>

57:11.719 --> 57:15.014
<i>We take everything and export them too.</i>

57:15.098 --> 57:17.559
<i>Waste? There's nothing that goes to waste!</i>

57:19.644 --> 57:21.354
<i>The cameras sure love you.</i>

57:21.438 --> 57:22.564
I can see why you were an actor.

57:30.864 --> 57:33.241
And these are the people
who died at the hands of Jung Seon-a,

57:33.324 --> 57:35.660
Chairwoman of
the Social Responsibility Foundation.

57:37.245 --> 57:38.705
Driven by her ambition,

57:42.083 --> 57:43.835
<i>she attacked me</i>

57:52.886 --> 57:54.888
and killed the innocent.

58:01.352 --> 58:04.564
And Min Jeong-ho, who was
appointed Chief Justice today

58:04.647 --> 58:08.443
is a hypocrite who acted as cat's paw
for Jung Seon-a, out of his own good.

58:09.277 --> 58:12.697
<i>He betrayed Inspector Yoon Su-hyeon
who was like a daughter to him,</i>

58:12.780 --> 58:16.117
and joined hands with Jung Seon-a
who killed her.

58:20.747 --> 58:22.624
Isn't it amazing?

58:52.403 --> 58:53.446
Now go…

59:01.955 --> 59:03.623
and live forever in hell.

59:05.500 --> 59:07.460
Your name will go down in history

59:09.087 --> 59:10.713
just as you wished.

59:58.928 --> 1:00:00.179
My fellow Koreans,

1:00:00.930 --> 1:00:02.307
are they guilty?

1:00:14.652 --> 1:00:20.491
INNOCENT, GUILTY

1:00:24.662 --> 1:00:27.040
But that's not fair! We're innocent.

1:00:28.041 --> 1:00:30.335
I guess we'll need
a fair punishment for them.

1:00:33.338 --> 1:00:34.964
What is that?

1:00:35.048 --> 1:00:36.549
Is that here?

1:00:36.633 --> 1:00:39.218
-What is that?
-What is that, Honey?

1:00:39.302 --> 1:00:41.763
<i>The moment you try and escape from here,</i>

1:00:41.846 --> 1:00:43.348
this bomb will go off.

1:00:44.223 --> 1:00:45.642
-He says it's a bomb!
-Go check.

1:00:45.725 --> 1:00:47.477
Honey!

1:00:54.734 --> 1:00:56.069
It's really here!

1:00:58.446 --> 1:01:01.616
Fellow Koreans, now you be the judge.

1:01:01.699 --> 1:01:04.952
I remember our President had
polled 10 million votes.

1:01:05.578 --> 1:01:09.123
The moment the number of votes
counted on Dike app reaches that number,

1:01:09.207 --> 1:01:12.043
you'll see a most grandiose firework show.

1:01:12.126 --> 1:01:14.337
To celebrate the victory of democracy.

1:01:18.341 --> 1:01:24.889
NO. OF PARTICIPANTS

1:02:01.634 --> 1:02:05.054
NO. OF PARTICIPANTS

1:02:08.349 --> 1:02:09.475
I'll be leaving now.

1:02:10.518 --> 1:02:11.894
Where to, Judge Kang?

1:02:15.398 --> 1:02:16.816
To the stage.

1:02:22.405 --> 1:02:25.032
The left door, facing the law school.

1:02:30.204 --> 1:02:32.081
The left door, facing the law school.

1:02:39.797 --> 1:02:41.424
Kang Yo-han, that bastard!

1:02:41.507 --> 1:02:43.134
Honey.

1:02:43.926 --> 1:02:45.595
It won't open?

1:02:46.345 --> 1:02:47.263
It won't.

1:02:51.350 --> 1:02:52.393
Honey.

1:02:55.271 --> 1:02:57.482
Oh, my…

1:02:58.316 --> 1:02:59.817
-Kang Yo-han!
-Oh, my.

1:03:03.780 --> 1:03:05.281
Take one more step,

1:03:06.407 --> 1:03:08.534
and I'll blow this place away.

1:03:23.132 --> 1:03:24.509
My fellow Koreans,

1:03:25.968 --> 1:03:28.429
the footages of
the Dream Base Hospital you just saw

1:03:29.138 --> 1:03:31.891
were filmed by Judge Kim Ga-on,
who risked his life to do so.

1:03:33.184 --> 1:03:34.977
<i>Once all of this is over,</i>

1:03:35.061 --> 1:03:38.856
<i>Judge Kim will testify the truth.</i>

1:03:39.774 --> 1:03:40.983
<i>As for the villains here,</i>

1:03:41.901 --> 1:03:44.153
they will be going to hell with me.

1:03:48.074 --> 1:03:49.492
No…

1:03:51.869 --> 1:03:52.912
Honey!

1:03:57.416 --> 1:04:00.378
Judge Kang. You ought to spare me.

1:04:02.088 --> 1:04:04.173
Didn't I do as you ordered?

1:04:05.341 --> 1:04:07.468
I brought them all here, didn't I?

1:04:20.273 --> 1:04:22.859
-Hello?
<i>-It's been a long time, President Min.</i>

1:04:24.610 --> 1:04:26.863
How did you call me?

1:04:26.946 --> 1:04:30.700
There's no time, so listen up.
I need you to do something for me.

1:04:30.783 --> 1:04:32.702
On the day of Min Jeong-ho's inauguration,

1:04:32.785 --> 1:04:35.746
have everyone at the Foundation
gather in the courtroom.

1:04:35.830 --> 1:04:37.039
<i>What?</i>

1:04:37.123 --> 1:04:38.624
What crazy nonsense…

1:04:38.708 --> 1:04:40.793
<i>Otherwise you'll die.</i>

1:04:40.877 --> 1:04:44.255
I have the evidence that you laid
your hands on the SRF's funds

1:04:45.590 --> 1:04:48.384
-to save Minbo Group from bankruptcy.
-Don't lie to me.

1:04:48.467 --> 1:04:50.553
If you can't believe me,
open the drawers under your desk.

1:04:51.220 --> 1:04:52.722
I put a copy in there.

1:04:53.848 --> 1:04:56.100
<i>So you dared to rob from them.</i>

1:04:58.769 --> 1:04:59.937
Help me.

1:05:00.605 --> 1:05:03.858
<i>-If they find out, I'm dead!</i>
-If you want to live, do as I say.

1:05:03.941 --> 1:05:05.026
Right now!

1:05:06.319 --> 1:05:08.529
You trashy bastard…

1:05:09.614 --> 1:05:11.908
You crazy bastard!

1:05:11.991 --> 1:05:13.451
Let go of me!

1:05:13.534 --> 1:05:14.911
How dare you!

1:05:17.413 --> 1:05:19.123
You psycho clown.

1:05:21.167 --> 1:05:22.376
You need to spare me.

1:05:23.210 --> 1:05:24.712
You need to spare me!

1:05:28.883 --> 1:05:32.595
All right, I'll at least give you
a chance since you traded with me.

1:05:38.935 --> 1:05:41.938
-The door's open.
-The door's open!

1:05:46.734 --> 1:05:47.860
Wouldn't you say

1:05:51.113 --> 1:05:53.324
this is a deja vu?

1:05:57.370 --> 1:05:59.705
Just like that time
at the cathedral ten years ago?

1:06:02.667 --> 1:06:04.251
Now run for your life.

1:06:04.919 --> 1:06:07.421
I'll take one, first-come, first-served.

1:06:20.726 --> 1:06:23.813
<i>I'll take one, first-come, first-served.</i>

1:06:44.333 --> 1:06:45.418
No!

1:08:44.870 --> 1:08:45.996
Yo-han…

1:08:50.000 --> 1:08:51.168
Yi-sak.

1:09:32.543 --> 1:09:33.544
Honey!

1:09:33.627 --> 1:09:37.047
-Hey, you bastard!
-Wait… Just be quiet!

1:09:37.131 --> 1:09:39.842
Wait, Kang Yo-han.

1:09:39.925 --> 1:09:42.344
How about we strike a deal?

1:09:42.428 --> 1:09:44.847
Quiet, all of you! Attention!

1:09:46.974 --> 1:09:48.184
Kang Yo-han.

1:09:50.352 --> 1:09:51.896
All you need to do is save me, all right?

1:09:51.979 --> 1:09:55.149
I'm the Chief of State!
It'll be a win-win deal for us!

1:09:55.733 --> 1:09:58.903
These guys are businessmen and women!

1:10:00.571 --> 1:10:02.448
But I'm different from them.

1:10:02.531 --> 1:10:04.491
What will this country do without me?

1:10:04.575 --> 1:10:06.493
I'm the Republic of Korea!

1:10:06.577 --> 1:10:09.788
I'm an artist and a leader.

1:10:09.872 --> 1:10:11.874
So please spare me this once.

1:10:11.957 --> 1:10:14.168
And this country too! Please!

1:10:14.251 --> 1:10:16.712
I… I'm the king, aren't I?

1:10:16.795 --> 1:10:18.714
Please! I'm the king!

1:10:18.797 --> 1:10:22.301
I'm the king, aren't I?

1:10:38.901 --> 1:10:42.321
Damn it, he's awfully loud.

1:11:06.470 --> 1:11:08.931
Shoot… Shoot him!

1:11:09.014 --> 1:11:10.975
Shoot!

1:11:11.058 --> 1:11:14.186
-Shoot him!
-Please shoot!

1:11:14.270 --> 1:11:15.688
Shoot him!

1:11:15.771 --> 1:11:17.815
You can do it, shoot him.

1:11:18.482 --> 1:11:19.358
Shoot him!

1:11:21.318 --> 1:11:23.195
So it comes down to us in the end, is it?

1:11:34.123 --> 1:11:36.333
Come with me, Seon-a.

1:12:07.531 --> 1:12:10.367
Goodbye, Young Master.

1:12:24.089 --> 1:12:27.801
Shit, just fuck this all.

1:13:36.537 --> 1:13:37.788
It's all right, Seon-a.

1:13:38.705 --> 1:13:39.748
It's okay.

1:13:55.472 --> 1:13:56.557
<i>Did you know?</i>

1:14:00.436 --> 1:14:05.065
<i>I really did love you, Young Master.</i>

1:14:44.104 --> 1:14:47.399
Please spare us, Judge Kang.

1:14:47.483 --> 1:14:49.067
Please spare us!

1:14:49.151 --> 1:14:52.613
Please spare us. Please…

1:14:52.696 --> 1:14:54.323
We're sorry.

1:14:57.075 --> 1:14:58.368
Judge Kang.

1:15:02.414 --> 1:15:03.665
Don't move.

1:15:04.458 --> 1:15:06.293
Why did you come here?

1:15:12.966 --> 1:15:14.343
You can't.

1:15:18.889 --> 1:15:20.849
Are you going to leave Elijah
to join them?

1:15:21.767 --> 1:15:23.268
With those trashy bastards?

1:15:28.649 --> 1:15:29.566
I can't help it.

1:15:30.400 --> 1:15:33.237
Once the show is over,
actors need to disappear from the stage.

1:16:11.024 --> 1:16:15.320
NUMBER OF PARTICIPANTS

1:16:20.158 --> 1:16:21.535
I'm coming with you then.

1:16:32.004 --> 1:16:33.630
You will be a hero.

1:16:35.507 --> 1:16:36.758
As for the devil,

1:16:38.135 --> 1:16:39.344
one is enough.

1:16:47.644 --> 1:16:49.187
Judge Kang.

1:16:49.855 --> 1:16:51.356
Judge Kang.

1:16:57.821 --> 1:16:59.615
Judge Kang!

1:17:11.752 --> 1:17:13.962
-Judge Kang! Kang Yo-han!
-It's dangerous!

1:17:26.558 --> 1:17:28.727
-Judge Kang.
-We're sorry.

1:17:28.810 --> 1:17:31.063
Don't do it!

1:17:40.614 --> 1:17:42.532
Kang Yo-han!

1:19:07.409 --> 1:19:11.872
No!

1:19:32.934 --> 1:19:34.728
Judge Kim, are you all right?

1:19:36.521 --> 1:19:37.814
The ambulance is here.

1:19:38.648 --> 1:19:40.650
Let's go. Do you think you can stand up?

1:20:25.403 --> 1:20:26.530
Elijah.

1:20:30.784 --> 1:20:31.827
Elijah?

1:20:59.145 --> 1:21:00.272
How about this one?

1:21:15.954 --> 1:21:17.122
Are you all right?

1:21:35.932 --> 1:21:37.893
You thought I'd really topple it, did you?

1:21:49.738 --> 1:21:52.240
BLUEPRINT

1:21:54.242 --> 1:21:57.787
SECURE EMERGENCY EXIT
HOW MUCH TIME IS AVAILABLE?

1:22:00.832 --> 1:22:04.002
MUST CHECKLIST

1:22:04.085 --> 1:22:08.048
CHECK DOUBLE LOCKS
CHECK DISTANCE

1:22:11.259 --> 1:22:13.887
<i>What is concentrated is easy to topple.</i>

1:22:15.388 --> 1:22:18.683
<i>Once the show is over,
the magician must disappear.</i>

1:22:25.106 --> 1:22:26.691
<i>I'm done cleaning up,</i>

1:22:28.109 --> 1:22:30.403
<i>and I believe there's now work
for you to do.</i>

1:22:36.993 --> 1:22:38.370
Ma'am.

1:22:38.954 --> 1:22:41.957
Master Yo-han dropped by.

1:22:43.333 --> 1:22:46.044
What happened? And where is Elijah?

1:22:47.587 --> 1:22:49.005
You see…

1:22:56.846 --> 1:22:58.181
Young Master!

1:22:59.265 --> 1:23:01.101
Young Master, you were alive!

1:23:01.184 --> 1:23:04.145
-Were you worried about me?
-Of course, do you need to ask?

1:23:04.938 --> 1:23:06.064
Listen.

1:23:06.606 --> 1:23:08.817
-You're fired as of today.
-Pardon?

1:23:09.484 --> 1:23:11.152
Leave this house and live your life.

1:23:11.236 --> 1:23:13.405
There won't be anyone here anymore.

1:23:13.488 --> 1:23:15.281
What do you mean, exactly?

1:23:18.785 --> 1:23:20.036
Young Master?

1:23:28.086 --> 1:23:30.714
-Elijah is in her room, is she?
-Yes.

1:23:31.923 --> 1:23:33.425
Young Master.

1:23:52.777 --> 1:23:53.945
Elijah.

1:24:02.454 --> 1:24:03.788
Yo-han.

1:24:16.634 --> 1:24:18.428
Are you out of prison now?

1:24:19.137 --> 1:24:20.221
Are you okay?

1:24:21.264 --> 1:24:24.601
Yes, you don't need to
worry anymore. I'm fine.

1:24:26.811 --> 1:24:28.521
We'll be going somewhere safe now.

1:24:30.148 --> 1:24:31.274
Somewhere safe?

1:24:31.858 --> 1:24:33.318
Should I show you where?

1:24:39.574 --> 1:24:41.534
It's a rehabilitation clinic
in Switzerland.

1:24:43.661 --> 1:24:48.041
I've been making donations
to find a way for you to walk again.

1:24:55.632 --> 1:24:56.883
Should we go here?

1:24:58.968 --> 1:25:00.470
Just the two of us?

1:25:03.223 --> 1:25:04.974
Yo-han.

1:25:40.593 --> 1:25:42.011
So he's alive.

1:25:44.305 --> 1:25:45.306
Thank goodness.

1:25:47.809 --> 1:25:51.563
But it looks like
I'll be busier from now on.

1:25:52.272 --> 1:25:53.273
Pardon?

1:25:53.356 --> 1:25:56.943
Young Master set up a health foods
e-commerce business for me,

1:25:57.026 --> 1:25:58.653
telling me it's my severance pay.

1:26:00.822 --> 1:26:04.242
He told me to sell lots of
healthy and not so tasty foods.

1:26:05.535 --> 1:26:07.162
Is he dissing me or what?

1:26:15.753 --> 1:26:17.505
<i>Are you really going back
to your hometown?</i>

1:26:17.589 --> 1:26:21.801
Yes, it'll be unfair to let just
Seoul have a taste of my charisma.

1:26:22.510 --> 1:26:26.723
-That's true.
-I volunteered for the Youth Court.

1:26:27.473 --> 1:26:30.602
I thought maybe I could lecture
and help troublemakers.

1:26:31.269 --> 1:26:34.397
-I thought I'd be pretty good at it.
-I'm sure you'll be.

1:26:34.480 --> 1:26:35.940
As always.

1:26:38.443 --> 1:26:39.861
Thank you for all your work.

1:26:41.529 --> 1:26:43.031
Same to you too.

1:26:43.114 --> 1:26:45.116
Call me if you're ever in the area.

1:27:00.423 --> 1:27:04.052
PUBLIC HEARING ON JUDICIAL REFORMS
FOLLOWING THE KANG YO-HAN CASE

1:27:07.889 --> 1:27:09.682
We, the new ruling party,

1:27:09.766 --> 1:27:14.020
vow to never repeat the mistakes
made by the Heo Joong-se government.

1:27:14.771 --> 1:27:17.232
So to restore the rule of law,

1:27:17.315 --> 1:27:19.567
I've invited all of you here today.

1:27:21.069 --> 1:27:23.446
First and foremost,
let's give a big hand to

1:27:24.030 --> 1:27:26.991
Judge Kim Ga-on, our national hero!

1:27:40.672 --> 1:27:45.635
Judge Kim,
what can we possibly do to prevent

1:27:46.636 --> 1:27:49.347
the disgraceful case of Kang Yo-han?

1:27:51.683 --> 1:27:53.268
Was that a disgraceful case?

1:27:54.936 --> 1:27:58.982
Kang Yo-han is not a hero,
but neither is he a criminal.

1:27:59.649 --> 1:28:02.860
Do you really think
our people raved about him

1:28:02.944 --> 1:28:05.196
because they are foolish
and are easily swayed?

1:28:07.198 --> 1:28:10.076
Is it because you're still young?
You sure are hot-blooded.

1:28:11.244 --> 1:28:14.747
In other words, you're suggesting
we need to address the root cause,

1:28:14.831 --> 1:28:16.040
but of course
we can't reach in short term.

1:28:18.042 --> 1:28:20.545
First we need to announce a measure

1:28:20.628 --> 1:28:22.839
that has an impact
to appease the angry citizens.

1:28:23.923 --> 1:28:25.675
I agree, Assemblyman.

1:28:25.758 --> 1:28:29.220
The Prosecution proposes
the rights of judicial appointment

1:28:29.304 --> 1:28:32.098
to the Ministry of Justice
to reinforce the nomination process

1:28:32.181 --> 1:28:35.435
and to filter out possible terrorists
like Kang Yo-han--

1:28:35.518 --> 1:28:37.228
That's nonsense!

1:28:37.312 --> 1:28:39.272
It'll be violating
our judicial independence.

1:28:39.355 --> 1:28:41.316
Assemblyman, rather than that,

1:28:41.399 --> 1:28:44.402
I propose newly launching
the Department of Live Court Show

1:28:44.485 --> 1:28:48.406
with Judge Kim Ga-on who's popular
as the new presiding--

1:28:48.489 --> 1:28:49.574
If you have time for this…

1:28:51.909 --> 1:28:53.369
Pardon?

1:28:53.453 --> 1:28:55.621
Shouldn't we rather focus on
what we need to do?

1:28:58.333 --> 1:28:59.584
I apologize.

1:29:00.209 --> 1:29:02.045
Please excuse my arrogance,

1:29:02.128 --> 1:29:04.714
but I must say this in front of
all my mentors. Please forgive me.

1:29:10.720 --> 1:29:11.929
We are all here

1:29:12.597 --> 1:29:15.725
to do our duties bestowed upon us
by our people, who is the sovereign.

1:29:16.476 --> 1:29:18.102
We must ensure no one is wronged,

1:29:18.978 --> 1:29:21.606
and that no one sheds tears of blood.

1:29:21.689 --> 1:29:26.194
We must also ensure those who make others
cry tears of blood is rightfully punished.

1:29:27.236 --> 1:29:28.571
Is that not our duty?

1:29:29.947 --> 1:29:31.949
That is why I'm in my judge's robe.

1:29:35.286 --> 1:29:38.915
If we fail to neglect our duties,
someone out there will suffer.

1:29:38.998 --> 1:29:40.291
And their suffering

1:29:41.709 --> 1:29:43.336
is what breeds monsters.

1:29:45.171 --> 1:29:47.048
There is a reason

1:29:47.965 --> 1:29:49.425
why people are enraged.

1:29:51.803 --> 1:29:54.180
Those are great words.

1:29:54.263 --> 1:29:57.016
We need our young talents
to be firm and resolute.

1:29:57.100 --> 1:29:58.392
I respect your views.

1:29:59.977 --> 1:30:01.938
Now that we've heard from Judge Kim,

1:30:02.021 --> 1:30:05.817
how about we now start discussing
the practical matters, Chairman?

1:30:05.900 --> 1:30:06.901
Yes, let's do that.

1:30:06.984 --> 1:30:09.987
You just mentioned the nomination process…

1:30:24.168 --> 1:30:25.419
<i>It's still the same.</i>

1:30:27.004 --> 1:30:28.798
<i>Nothing has changed after all.</i>

